sparql_query_kg2:
To produce a SPARQL query for KG2 (Wikidata) that corresponds to the given Natural Language Question "Give me the birthdays of all actors of the television show Charmed," we first need to analyze the given information and examples.

Given the information:

* Knowledge Graph 1 Name: DBpedia
* Knowledge Graph 2 Name: Wikidata
* Entity and Relation Mapping (ER2):
	+ {
	  "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charmed",
	  "wikidata_ids": [
	    "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q162371"
	  ]
	},
	+ {
	  "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/starring",
	  "wikidata_ids": [
	    "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P161"
	  ]
	},
	+ {
	  "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/birthDate",
	  "wikidata_ids": [
	    "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P569"
	  ]
	}

We can see that the relation between Charmed and its actors is mapped to Wikidata property P161, and the birth date is mapped to Wikidata property P569.

The corresponding SPARQL query for KG2 (Wikidata) can be constructed as follows:

<sparql>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT ?date
WHERE 
{
	?actor wdt:P161 wd:Q162371 .
	?actor wdt:P569 ?date .
}
</sparql>

This query will select the birth dates of all actors of the television show Charmed.

